.TH LPF-TOOLS 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.3.0" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-tools \- emit tool\-calling schemas for AI agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf tools [\-\-format openai|jsonschema|system\-prompt]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Emit JSON tool\-calling schemas for automation agents that need to call lpf commands.
The output is generated from the same OCaml command metadata used for help text and man pages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-format openai
emit OpenAI\-style tool schema objects; this is the default
.TP
\-\-format jsonschema
emit standalone JSON Schema objects
.TP
\-\-format system\-prompt
emit a JSON string containing a compact lpf automation prompt
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf tools
lpf tools \-\-format jsonschema
lpf tools \-\-format system\-prompt
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only and must not include host inventory or credentials.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-man(8), lpf\-check(8)
